  "texts": [
    "We run an instance of PsyCoRe at psycore.one, and it is this instance to which the Constructor Shiny App submits new DCT specifications.",
    "This submission process consists of a pushed Git commit which triggers the execution of a number of commands using either GitLab's continuous integration / continuous deployment functionality (in our original version) or that triggers a bash script on the server (in our current implementation).",
    "The server or Codeberg/Git-Lab Pages runner then runs Quarto or Hugo to rebuild the website.",
    "Quarto or Hugo then integrates all data from the DCT specifications in the YAML files (including any newly committed files) in the overviews and construct pages.",
    "In our implementation, the Git commit causes a webhook on our own server to be called, which then pulls the repository and runs Quarto."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}